column1:
1438|2:38 P.M.|2:38 P.M.
"Abdoullah" had finished unpacking the second crate
column2: and now he examined what he had: two fifteen-kiloton nuclear devices
column3: made using enriched uranium-235 from the Kahuta Nuclear Research Center. He smiled again to think they had been smuggled out right from under the noses of the officials at Kahuta
column4: directly up the security elevators leading down to the U235 centrifuge at Level Five.
